---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';
import { AUTHOR, SOCIALS } from '../data/site';
import { getRankedSpots } from '../lib/spots';

const spots = await getRankedSpots();
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description={`${AUTHOR.bio} Hoji Ben is the hub for hojicha in San Francisco: honest, unsponsored rankings of every spot in the city.`}
  path="/about/"
  crumb="about"
  jsonLd={breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'About', path: '/about/' },
  ])}
>
  <div class="head">
    <span class="title mono">about</span>
    <span class="head-meta mono muted">{spots.length} spots logged</span>
  </div>

  <div class="pad">
    <div class="who">
      <img src={AUTHOR.avatar} alt={AUTHOR.name} width="44" height="44" />
      <div>
        <p class="who-name">{AUTHOR.name}</p>
        <p class="who-handle mono muted">{AUTHOR.handle} · san francisco</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mono muted">// what this is</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      I drink a lot of hojicha. At some point I started writing down which San
      Francisco spots do it well, and this turned into the list.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mono muted">// the idea</h2>
    <p>
      I kept wanting one place to look up where to get a good hojicha in the
      city and couldn't find it, so I'm making it. Every spot gets the same
      routine: order it, drink it, give it a letter grade, post the video.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mono muted">// why hojicha</h2>
    <p>
      Roasted green tea. Toasty and nutty instead of grassy, and lower in
      caffeine than coffee or matcha. New to it? Start with{' '}
      <a href="/articles/what-is-hojicha/">what hojicha is</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mono muted">// how grading works</h2>
    <p>
      I look at roast, balance, sweetness, and how consistent it is from one
      visit to the next. The{' '}
      <a href="/">index</a>{' '}
      updates whenever I log a new spot. {spots.length} so far.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mono muted">// elsewhere</h2>
    <ul class="links mono">
      {
        SOCIALS.map((s) => (
          <li>
            <a href={s.url} target="_blank" rel="me noopener">
              {s.label.toLowerCase()} ↗
            </a>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--panel);
  }
  .title {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }
  .head-meta {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }
  .pad {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    max-width: 600px;
  }
  .who {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .who img {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  .who-name {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .who-handle {
    margin: 1px 0 0;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }
  .lede {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .pad p {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pad p a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--line-strong);
  }
  .links {
    list-style: none;
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }
  .links a {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .links a:hover {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
